headline: Should You Buy Bank of America While It's Below $45?
summary: As a leader in the financial services industry, Bank of America (NYSE: BAC) has its hands in a wide range of markets.  This includes consumer and commercial banking, capital markets, investment banking, and wealth management.  Bank of America may have the attention of those considering allocating capital to such an important part of the economy.

headline: BofA’s Holly O’Neill gets expanded role
summary: Bank of America is combining consumer units and giving one of its most senior women a bigger role leading the lender’s retail, consumer and preferred banking divisions.
